1. Come up with game idea
    Prompt: Crack in Reality
    The Power of Flex Tape
    "To show you the power of flex tape, I sawed the fabric of reality in half!"
    Tear in reality spits out cars
    [OPTIONAL] Spits out wind when you get close

2. Decide Win / Lose / Score Condition
    Goal = get to hole and patch it
    Make crack texture
    Make a particle emmitter that spits out cars
    Player gets knocked back when car touches him
    Player patches up hole and wins
    [OPTIONAL] Player has to patch in multiple spots
    [OPTIONAL] Patches take time to apply
    Lose = ???
        - Get hit by car too many times?
        - Dead Zone closes in?
        - Time Limit?

3. Flesh out assets
    Need:
    - Crack in Reality (could be transparent png or 3D model)
    - Cars (3D Model)
    - Player (Basic shapes with face texture)
    - Tape (3D Model)
    - [OPTIONAL] Wind (Particle System)
    - [OPTIONAL] BackGround City Skybox
    - [OPTIONAL] Background Buildings (A bunch of large cubes, prevents player from wandering)
    Sounds:
    - Car honking
    - Tape ripping
    - Etherial Void Sound (???)
    - Dramatic music
    - [OPTIONAL] Player jump / hurt noise
    UI:
    - [OPTIONAL] Health Bar / Timer (depends on lose condition)
    - Title Screen
    - Win Screen
    - [OPTIONAL] Tutorial Popup at start of game
        - Deactivates upon any movement
    - [OPTIONAL] Ranking on win screen
    - Lose Screen
    - [OPTIONAL] Intro Cinematic
4. Submit to itch

